<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 4:10PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Prairie and
southwestern Dawson Counties through 515 PM MDT...
At 410 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fallon, or 10 miles northeast of Terry, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Glendive, Terry, Fallon, West Glendive, Hoyt, Calypso, Forest Park
and Marsh.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
